1
00:00:03,180 --> 00:00:04,750
Where
are you taking us?

2
00:00:04,930 --> 00:00:06,450
Applejack:
we're almost there, youngins!

3
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,220
I've never been here
before.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:13,560
Ouch!

5
00:00:13,730 --> 00:00:15,010
Oh, sorry.

6
00:00:15,130 --> 00:00:16,510
Are we there yet?

7
00:00:16,810 --> 00:00:18,300
There? Where?
What?

8
00:00:18,610 --> 00:00:20,090
I don't even know
what we're doing!

9
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:21,390
Here we are!

10
00:00:21,580 --> 00:00:22,830
What are we
looking at?

11
00:00:23,050 --> 00:00:24,860
I have no idea.

12
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:26,130
What is
that thing?

13
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:30,760
Cutie Mark Crusaders,
welcome to your new clubhouse!

14
00:00:34,830 --> 00:00:36,570
Well, don't thank me
all at once.

15
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,500
This was my clubhouse
when I was your age.

16
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:42,450
Sure, it hasn't been used
in a while,

17
00:00:42,510 --> 00:00:43,630
But it's empty

18
00:00:43,660 --> 00:00:45,900
And on a secluded, private
part of the farm.

19
00:00:46,130 --> 00:00:47,330
And it's all yours.

20
00:00:47,370 --> 00:00:48,720
[ Crash ]

21
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:51,300
It just needs
a little, uh, TLC.

22
00:00:51,470 --> 00:00:54,890
TLC as in "Tender Loving Care"
or "Totally Lost Cause"?

23
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:57,710
Applejack,
we're supposed to turn this

24
00:00:57,740 --> 00:00:59,530
Into
our new clubhouse?

25
00:00:59,690 --> 00:01:01,740
Well, maybe y'all will get
your cutie marks

26
00:01:01,790 --> 00:01:04,220
When you discover
your talent for -- Aah!

27
00:01:06,730 --> 00:01:07,240
Ugh.

28
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,430
House cleaning?

29
00:01:15,270 --> 00:01:20,270
Hard of Hearing subtitles
by YayPonies
https://yp1.yayponies.no/

30
00:02:09,540 --> 00:02:10,530
[ All gasp ]

31
00:02:14,550 --> 00:02:16,050
Not so fast!

32
00:02:33,790 --> 00:02:36,170
[ Tires screech ]

33
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:38,450
Whoa!
Hey, Scootaloo.

34
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,430
Back already?

35
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,360
You're amazing
on that scooter.

36
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:43,870
Thanks.
Wow, Apple Bloom.

37
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,080
You did all of this?
Yep.

38
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:48,930
I fixed the broken shutters,
sanded off the splinters,

39
00:02:48,990 --> 00:02:50,800
Rebuilt the roof, painted.

40
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:52,610
That's so cool!

41
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,000
What's Sweetie Belle
up to?

42
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:58,770
* we are
the Cutie Mark Crusaders *

43
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:02,760
[ Humming ]

44
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:05,940
* never stop the journey

45
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,540
[ Humming ]

46
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,030
Apple Bloom:
there you are, Sweetie Belle!

47
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:11,470
See?
I told you we could find her

48
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,750
By following
her totally awesome voice.

49
00:03:13,910 --> 00:03:15,740
What's that sweet tune
you're singing?

50
00:03:15,950 --> 00:03:19,890
Oh. I was just working on our
new Cutie Mark Crusaders
theme song.

51
00:03:20,170 --> 00:03:21,570
Cool!
Cool!

52
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:22,790
Teach us?

53
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:26,590
Well, I've only come up
with one part, but, okay!

54
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:30,730
* they all say
that you will get your mark *

55
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:34,700
* when the time
is really right *

56
00:03:35,010 --> 00:03:38,990
* and you know just
what you're supposed to do *

57
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:42,020
* and your talent
comes to light! *

58
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:46,410
Well, I'll be,
Cutie Mark Crusaders.

59
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:48,690
You've done one fine job
with this place.

60
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,080
So, what's next?

61
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:52,890
Well, now that we have
a real-Life clubhouse...

62
00:03:52,980 --> 00:03:54,700
and a map
of Ponyville...

63
00:03:54,770 --> 00:03:57,210
and a Cutie Mark Crusaders
theme song...

64
00:03:57,340 --> 00:03:58,150
theme song?

65
00:03:58,390 --> 00:03:59,530
We're gonna go out in the world

66
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:00,940
And discover our talents!

67
00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:02,490
A new adventure!

68
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:04,320
And earn
our cutie marks!

69
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:06,000
We'll leave no stone unturned!

70
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:08,070
No mountain unclimbed!

71
00:04:08,170 --> 00:04:09,800
No meal uncooked!

72
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:11,380
No song unlearned!

73
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:12,590
Well, okay, then!

74
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:15,060
[ Sighs ]
sounds like you have a plan.

75
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:18,790
I got to, uh,
leave no apple unpicked.

76
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,190
See y'all later.

77
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,590
Are we ready to get
our cutie marks, ponies?

78
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:24,540
Ready!
Ready!

79
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:39,600
[ Bell rings ]

80
00:04:42,670 --> 00:04:44,810
[ Pigs squealing ]

81
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:04,310
[ Sniffs ]

82
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:21,970
[ Whirring ]

83
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:40,720
[ Bell dinging ]

84
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:47,960
[ Sobbing ]

85
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:32,430
[ Ding! ]

86
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:52,710
[ Wind whistling ]

87
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,450
I had nothing to do
with this.

88
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:23,840
What is going on here?

89
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:24,810
Hmm.

90
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,820
Well, we sure aren't getting
our cutie marks

91
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:28,110
For being librarians.

92
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,850
Huh.
I should think not.

93
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:31,120
What?

94
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:34,050
Girls, I think you're going
about this the wrong way.

95
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,300
Instead of trying to do things

96
00:07:35,340 --> 00:07:36,790
In areas
you're not familiar with,

97
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:39,190
Why not try doing things
in areas that you already like?

98
00:07:39,690 --> 00:07:42,090
And I have the perfect place
to start.

99
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:45,670
Showcase your talents...

100
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:46,720
for all to see.

101
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:49,780
Perform in the Ponyville
school talent show!

102
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,840
There will be
all sorts of awards --

103
00:07:51,910 --> 00:07:55,250
Best dramatic performance,
best comedy act, best magic act.

104
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:57,390
Surely you can find
your talent.

105
00:07:57,740 --> 00:08:00,560
This would be the perfect place
to discover our talents!

106
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:01,360
Juggling!

107
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,080
Acting!

108
00:08:02,140 --> 00:08:03,300
Magic tricks!

109
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,420
Square dancing!

110
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:05,650
Tight-Rope walking!

111
00:08:05,690 --> 00:08:06,730
Tiger taming!

112
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,520
My little ponies,
you're missing the point.

113
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:12,450
Think about the things
you already enjoy doing.

114
00:08:12,710 --> 00:08:14,560
Think about
what you're already good at.

115
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:16,360
Sure.
We could do that.

116
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:17,830
Yeah, sure we can.

117
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,610
Well, whatever we do,
we'll do it as...

118
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:23,410
all:
the Cutie Mark Crusaders!

119
00:08:29,370 --> 00:08:30,610
Sweetie Belle!

120
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:33,280
I told you not to touch
my things!

121
00:08:33,530 --> 00:08:35,520
Come back
with my supplies!

122
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:37,820
We're just borrowing them
for the talent show.

123
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,370
Don't worry, sis!

124
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:41,290
I promise
we'll bring them back!

125
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,750
Thanks, mr. Breezy.

126
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:46,980
We're return the fan to you
real soon.

127
00:08:48,450 --> 00:08:50,030
What do we need
this fan for?

128
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:51,560
Trust me on this one.

129
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:57,290
Okay, so that's six wooden
planks, 4x8 plywood,

130
00:08:57,320 --> 00:09:00,180
A box of nails, four cans
of paint, and four brushes.

131
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:01,110
Anything else?

132
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:02,540
Yeah.

133
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:05,450
Instructions on how to use
six wooden planks,

134
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:08,300
4x8 plywood, a box of nails,
four cans of paint,

135
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,290
And four brushes.

136
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:13,750
Whoa!

137
00:09:14,130 --> 00:09:16,400
"Ghosts, goblins,
and ghoulish figures"?

138
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:17,870
Good heavens, girls.

139
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:19,660
What do you need
a book like this for?

140
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:21,750
You'll see.
Thanks, Twilight.

141
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,050
We'll give it back as soon
as we're done with it!

142
00:09:24,350 --> 00:09:25,860
What do you think
they're up to?

143
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:27,090
I have no idea,

144
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:29,980
And I don't know if I should be
excited or scared to find out.

145
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:33,290
Apple Bloom: I'm glad
we're doing this as a team.

146
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:34,580
Me too!

147
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:37,170
Um, so,
what are we doing again?

148
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:41,040
A super, awesome, dramatic song
for the talent show, of course.

149
00:09:41,290 --> 00:09:41,740
Right!

150
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:45,310
With super-Cool scenery
and amazing costumes!

151
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,580
And mind-Blowing
dance moves.

152
00:09:47,850 --> 00:09:50,060
This is gonna be
so amazing.

153
00:09:50,450 --> 00:09:52,740
Sweetie Belle, I think
you should be the singer.

154
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:53,500
What?

155
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:55,790
No way I'm singing
in front of a crowd.

156
00:09:56,020 --> 00:09:58,360
Twilight said to do something
we like to do,

157
00:09:58,570 --> 00:10:00,950
And I'd like to be
like my big sister,

158
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,540
And she's a designer.

159
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,330
Fine, then. You can do
the costumes and the scenery.

160
00:10:05,420 --> 00:10:05,900
Mm-Hmm.

161
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:08,660
And, Scootaloo, you're great
at maneuvers on your scooter,

162
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:10,390
So you should do
the choreography.

163
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:12,630
You know,
all those dance moves.

164
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:14,580
[ Gasps ]

165
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:16,620
Nah.

166
00:10:16,690 --> 00:10:18,790
I'd rather sing
a wicked rock ballad.

167
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:22,150
Why don't you come up with the
dance routine, Apple Bloom?

168
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,630
Hmm.

169
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:27,980
I'm not much of a dancer,
but I do like kung fu!

170
00:10:28,110 --> 00:10:29,470
That's kind of like dancing!

171
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,680
Hyah! Hah!

172
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,610
Hah! Yah!

173
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,010
Then it's settled!

174
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,740
Let's get started!

175
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:42,990
[ Music playing ]

176
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,840
One, two, three, oh!

177
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:47,690
Oh!

178
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,460
Ow, Apple Bloom!

179
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:50,700
What are you doing?

180
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:52,960
[ Groans ]

181
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,990
I feel like I have
four left feet.

182
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:57,350
I can't even spin right.

183
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:58,720
Don't be silly.

184
00:10:58,790 --> 00:11:00,230
You just got to keep
your head forward

185
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:02,280
Until the very last minute,
like this.

186
00:11:05,670 --> 00:11:07,630
See?
Easy peasy.

187
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,710
You just got to practice
a bunch, that's all.

188
00:11:09,810 --> 00:11:10,630
Wow!

189
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:13,020
That does look easy!
Thanks!

190
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:15,780
Okay.
Let's try this again.

191
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:19,940
Oh! Ouch!

192
00:11:20,330 --> 00:11:21,780
Ow!
[ Crash ]

193
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:23,250
I'm okay!

194
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,610
Keep practicing!

195
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:26,060
Will do!

196
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:28,260
[ Piano plays ]

197
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:30,500
[ Off-Key ] * we fight
the fight, walk the walk *

198
00:11:30,610 --> 00:11:35,470
* talk the talk, eat the, uh,
food like a celery stalk? *

199
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:37,340
Ugh!

200
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:39,890
I'll never come up
with anything!

201
00:11:40,050 --> 00:11:41,900
Never, never, never!

202
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:46,320
Come back! Come back!

203
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:48,990
Dumb fabric.

204
00:11:49,650 --> 00:11:51,670
Hey, scoot.
How's the song going?

205
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,250
Pbht!

206
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,680
Pbht?
Oh, my.

207
00:11:55,810 --> 00:11:56,910
Sounds serious.

208
00:11:57,210 --> 00:11:59,040
I'm just no good
at lyrics.

209
00:11:59,140 --> 00:12:03,100
Coming up with words
is like...really hard.

210
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:05,100
Oh,
they can't be that bad.

211
00:12:05,990 --> 00:12:09,010
"With our cutie marks
we'll rock Equestria.

212
00:12:09,290 --> 00:12:12,340
We use our stomachs
to digestia"?

213
00:12:14,010 --> 00:12:17,710
Um, well,
these are, um, good,

214
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:20,900
But how about
after "we fight the fight"...

215
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:24,690
* there is nothing
that we fear *

216
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:28,490
* we'll have to figure out
what we'll do next *

217
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:32,580
* till our cutie marks
are here *

218
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,430
Wow!
That's so awesome!

219
00:12:35,570 --> 00:12:37,290
Did you just come up
with that now?

220
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:39,270
Yeah, kind of.

221
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:40,120
Thanks!

222
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,820
I'm totally using that.

223
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:51,290
Oh, no!

224
00:12:58,180 --> 00:13:04,920
[ Whirring ]

225
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,930
[ Whirring stops ]

226
00:13:06,070 --> 00:13:09,120
One, two, three, four, five?

227
00:13:09,970 --> 00:13:11,110
Oh!

228
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,210
[ Sighs ]

229
00:13:14,390 --> 00:13:15,370
Ouch!

230
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,600
How's the spin
coming along?

231
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,220
I think I got to just stick
to punches and kicks.

232
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:25,200
You know
ponies only have four legs?

233
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,500
Unh.

234
00:13:26,820 --> 00:13:29,720
I'll never be a designer
like my sister, Rarity.

235
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,490
Hey,
it's no big deal.

236
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,070
Why don't you use
the dress form?

237
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:35,600
It'll help you
with your patterns

238
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,900
And help you put all the pieces
in the right places.

239
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,690
Oh.
Is that what that's for?

240
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:42,740
Uh, maybe you should also clean
your paint brush

241
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:43,970
Between each color.

242
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:47,590
Oh, I was wondering why all
the colors looked like mud.

243
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,700
You're not using power tools,
are you?

244
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:53,750
The talent show's
just around the corner.

245
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,440
I wonder how the fillies
are doing.

246
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:57,790
[ Upbeat music playing ]

247
00:13:57,890 --> 00:13:59,300
Oh, sorry, Scootaloo!

248
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,660
That's okay.
Ugh!

249
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:02,340
Oops!
Sorry, Scootaloo.

250
00:14:02,380 --> 00:14:03,020
Ouch!

251
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:04,760
Oh, my bad,
Sweetie Belle.

252
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,810
Let's sing
the chorus again.

253
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,450
Well, gosh.

254
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:12,370
Sure wasn't expecting that.

255
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,510
Apple Bloom: I think
that sounded pretty good.

256
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:16,890
Me too.
You think we're ready?

257
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:18,740
Ready as we'll ever be.

258
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,350
Hey,
did you see us practicing?

259
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,190
Uh, yeah.

260
00:14:23,490 --> 00:14:25,420
Well, how did we do?
How did we do?

261
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:27,130
Uh...

262
00:14:27,460 --> 00:14:29,160
speechless!
See, girls?

263
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,820
I told you that's what
we're gonna do.

264
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:33,030
We're gonna leave them
speechless!

265
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,810
Yay!
Yay!
